games.summary: Rookie VJ Edgecombe made the go-ahead follow shot with 0.9 seconds left, Tyrese Maxey raced back for a game-saving blocked shot and the Philadelphia 76ers beat the short-handed Golden State Warriors 99-98 on Thursday night. Golden State did get some good news on the injury front with the return of Melton, who had 14 points in his season debut while coming back from a torn ACL.
blurbs: 📋 Quentin Grimes (PHI) made just his 4th start this season. 12 pts, 5 reb.
🆕 Al Horford (GS) made his first start of the season. 18 min, 3 pts.
⬆️ Pat Spencer (GS) played 24 min (season avg: 13). 16 pts, 4 reb, 4 ast.

games.summary: Derrick White scored a season-high 30 points, Jordan Walsh added a career-high 22 and the Boston Celtics , playing without Jaylen Brown , routed the Washington Wizards 146-101 on Thursday night. Brown, who scored a season-high 42 points against the New York Knicks on Tuesday night, was out with an illness.
blurbs: 📋 Marvin Bagley III (WSH) made just his 4th start this season. 5 pts, 6 reb.
⬆️ Will Riley (WSH) played 27 min (season avg: 8). 7 pts, 4 reb, 2 ast.
📋 Sam Hauser (BOS) made just his 4th start this season. 6 pts, 2 reb.
⬆️ Jordan Walsh (BOS) played 30 min (season avg: 20). 22 pts, 7 reb, 3 ast.
⬆️ Baylor Scheierman (BOS) played 25 min (season avg: 12). 5 pts, 6 reb, 3 ast.

games.summary: Lauri Markkanen scored 30 points, Keyonte George had 29 and the Utah Jazz used a huge fourth quarter to beat the Brooklyn Nets 123-110 on Thursday night. Noah Clowney scored 29 points and Ziaire Williams had 23 off the bench for Nets, who had their two-game winning streak snapped.

Rui Hachimura made a 3-pointer off a pass from LeBron James as time expired to give the Los Angeles Lakers a 123-120 victory over the Toronto Raptors on Thursday night. The assist to Hachimura ensured that James’ NBA-record streak of 1,297 consecutive double-digit scoring games in the regular season ended.
blurbs: 📋 Sandro Mamukelashvili (TOR) made just his 2nd start this season. 13 pts, 8 reb.
📋 Ja'Kobe Walter (TOR) made just his 5th start this season. 17 pts, 3 reb.
📋 Gabe Vincent (LAL) made just his 4th start this season. 5 pts, 2 reb.

games.summary: Julius Randle had 28 points and nine rebounds, carrying Minnesota on a quiet night from Anthony Edwards , and the Timberwolves beat the New Orleans Pelicans 125-116 on Thursday night. He scored a season-high 44 points on Tuesday in Minnesota's 146-142 overtime victory in the opener of the two-game set.
blurbs: 📋 Bryce McGowens (NO) made just his 4th start this season. 15 pts, 3 reb.
